# Context7 CLI (Focus-selected only)

**Do not use unless Focus/Meta selected Context7** for this turn (Context Plan or
explicit domain-implementation need). Prefer repo docs (`MODULE.md`, ADRs,
`docs/integrations/`) when they already answer the question.

**Use for:** library/framework/SDK API syntax, version-specific migration notes,
and framework recipes while implementing domain executor work (`backend`,
`integrations`, `data-platform`, `ui-ux`, `machine-learning`).

**Do not use for:** ad-hoc chat, refactor-only, code review, product/policy prose,
general programming concepts, or when repo docs already suffice.

## Commands

1. `npx ctx7@latest library <name> "<question>"` — resolve `/org/project` id
2. `npx ctx7@latest docs <libraryId> "<question>"` — one concept per query; ≤3 cmds

Auth: `npx ctx7@latest login` or `CONTEXT7_API_KEY`. On quota failure, tell the user
— do not silently fall back to training data when docs were required.

Catalog entry: [skill-catalog](../skills/skill-catalog/SKILL.md) `catalog.cliDocs`.
